      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "Note so I don't forget about this:\r\n\r\nBy chance I came across:\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/c006ab29ceec9274dc85a0de7f7d0502021a4b87/ci/test/04_install.sh#L28-L30\r\n\r\nWhich adds the `CAP_SYS_PTRACE` capability to the docker container being started. If we'd run the functional tests in docker we use `--cap-add BPF` (assuming a 5.8+ kernel). \r\n\r\n[docker docs: Runtime privilege and Linux capabilities](https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/run/#runtime-privilege-and-linux-capabilities)",
